  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mechanical Supervisor",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Supervise and coordinate mechanical maintenance, installation, and repair activities</p></li><li><p>Assign tasks and monitor performance of mechanical technicians and contractors</p></li><li><p>Ensure machinery, equipment, and systems operate efficiently and safely</p></li><li><p>Read and interpret mechanical drawings, blueprints, and technical manuals</p></li><li><p>Schedule preventive maintenance and oversee corrective maintenance activities</p></li><li><p>Enforce safety policies, procedures, and compliance with regulations</p></li><li><p>Inspect completed work to ensure quality standards are met</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot mechanical issues and implement effective solutions</p></li><li><p>Maintain maintenance records, reports, and inventory of tools and spare parts</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with engineering, production, and management teams</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Qualifications & Skills</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Proven experience as a Mechanical Supervisor or similar role</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of mechanical systems, tools, and equipment</p></li><li><p>Ability to lead and motivate a team</p></li><li><p>Excellent problem-solving and troubleshooting skills</p></li><li><p>Good communication and organizational abilities</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of safety standards and maintenance best practices</p></li></ul>",
